        Bayerische Motoren Werke AG

        Luxury vehicles company

        Description

        Description

        Bayerische Motoren Werke AG, commonly referred to as BMW, is a German multinational company which produces luxury vehicles and motorcycles. The company was founded in 1916 as a manufacturer of aircraft engines, which it produced from 1917 until 1918 and again from 1933 to 1945. Wikipedia
        Founded: 7 March 1916, Munich, Germany
        Stock price: BMW (ETR) €72.10 0.00 (0.00%)
        22 Dec, 5:35 pm GMT+1 - Disclaimer
        Customer service: 1800 102 2269
        Headquarters: Munich, Germany
        Subsidiaries: BMW M, Rolls-Royce Motor Cars, BMW India, MORE
        Founders: Karl Rapp, Camillo Castiglioni, Gustav Otto, Franz Josef Popp
